    "description": "<p>A spear is a polearm consisting of a shaft, usually of wood, with a pointed head. The head may be simply the sharpened end of the shaft itself or it may be made of a more durable material fastened to the shaft. The spear has been used throughout history as a weapon for hunting and/or fishing and for warfare. <span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Spears are typically 1.8 to 2.5m in length.</span></p>",
